Where Are ChatGPT's Data Centers?

OpenAI does not operate from a single data center.

Historically, ChatGPT primarily ran on Microsoft Azure AI supercomputers built for OpenAI. 
Today, OpenAI also uses infrastructure from multiple providers, including Microsoft Azure, Oracle, CoreWeave, and Google Cloud for different computing needs.

Some major locations include:

| Country  | Location             | Infrastructure                                         |
| -------- | -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| 🇺🇸 USA | Texas                | Large AI data centers (Stargate project)               |
| 🇺🇸 USA | Iowa                 | Microsoft Azure infrastructure                         |
| 🇺🇸 USA | Virginia             | Microsoft Azure infrastructure                         |
| 🇺🇸 USA | Washington State     | Microsoft cloud infrastructure                         |
| 🇺🇸 USA | Other U.S. locations | Oracle, CoreWeave, and additional cloud infrastructure |


========

Why Are Most Data Centers in the USA?

Because OpenAI is an American company.

The United States has:

Huge cloud infrastructure
Reliable electricity
High-speed fiber networks
Large AI GPU clusters
Major cloud providers such as Microsoft, Oracle, Google, and Amazon
What Is the Stargate Project?

In 2025, OpenAI announced the Stargate Project, a massive AI infrastructure initiative
with partners including Oracle, SoftBank, and MGX to build large AI data centers in the United States. 
The announced investment is up to US$500 billion over several years.

